backend :
1.  application.properties        ← database connection, JWT secret
2.  Role.java                     ← enum (ADMIN, ANALYST, VIEWER)
3.  MatchStatus.java              ← enum (MATCHED, PARTIAL, etc)
4.  UploadStatus.java             ← enum (PROCESSING, COMPLETED, FAILED)
5.  User.java                     ← model/entity
6.  UploadJob.java                ← model/entity
7.  TransactionRecord.java        ← model/entity
8.  ReconciliationResult.java     ← model/entity
9.  AuditLog.java                 ← model/entity
10. UserRepository.java           ← just an interface, Spring writes SQL for you
11. UploadJobRepository.java      ← interface
12. TransactionRecordRepository   ← interface
13. ReconciliationResultRepository← interface
14. AuditLogRepository.java       ← interface
15. JwtUtil.java                  ← generates and validates JWT tokens
16. CustomUserDetailsService.java ← loads user from DB for Spring Security
17. JwtFilter.java                ← checks JWT on every request
18. SecurityConfig.java           ← which URLs need login, which are public
19. DataInitializer.java          ← seeds 3 default users on startup
20. AuditService.java             ← saves audit log entries
21. ReconciliationEngine.java     ← matching logic (MATCHED/PARTIAL/etc)
22. FileProcessingService.java    ← reads CSV/Excel, saves rows to DB
23. AuthController.java           ← POST /api/auth/login
24. UploadController.java         ← POST /api/upload/submit
25. ReconciliationController.java ← GET /api/reconciliation/results
26. AuditController.java          ← GET /api/audit


frontend:

1.  index.js                 ← entry point
2.  App.js                   ← routes
3.  services/api.js          ← all axios calls in one place
4.  context/AuthContext.js   ← login state available everywhere
5.  components/Auth/Login.js ← login form
6.  components/Layout.js     ← sidebar + header shell
7.  components/Dashboard.js  ← charts and summary numbers
8.  components/FileUpload.js ← drag and drop + column mapping
9.  components/Reconciliation.js ← results table
10. components/AuditTrail.js ← timeline